Here's the standard approach for runtime theme switching in .NET MAUI:

## 1. Define Resource Dictionaries for each theme

```xml
<!-- Themes/LightTheme.xaml -->
<ResourceDictionary xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui"
                    xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml">
    <Color x:Key="PageBackground">#FFFFFF</Color>
    <Color x:Key="TextPrimary">#1A1A1A</Color>
    <Color x:Key="AccentColor">#0078D4</Color>
</ResourceDictionary>
```

Create similar files for `DarkTheme.xaml` and `HighContrastTheme.xaml`.

## 2. Merge a default theme in `App.xaml`

```xml
<Application.Resources>
    <ResourceDictionary>
        <ResourceDictionary.MergedDictionaries>
            <local:LightTheme />
        </ResourceDictionary.MergedDictionaries>
    </ResourceDictionary>
</Application.Resources>
```

## 3. Create a theme service to swap dictionaries at runtime

```csharp
public static class ThemeService
{
    public static void ApplyTheme(string theme)
    {
        var mergedDicts = Application.Current.Resources.MergedDictionaries;
        mergedDicts.Clear();

        mergedDicts.Add(theme switch
        {
            "Dark"         => new DarkTheme(),
            "HighContrast" => new HighContrastTheme(),
            _              => new LightTheme()
        });

        // Persist the choice
        Preferences.Set("AppTheme", theme);
    }
}
```

## 4. Call it from your settings page

```csharp
// In your SettingsPage or ViewModel
void OnThemeSelected(string selectedTheme)
{
    ThemeService.ApplyTheme(selectedTheme);
}
```

## 5. Restore on startup in `App.xaml.cs`

```csharp
public App()
{
    InitializeComponent();
    ThemeService.ApplyTheme(Preferences.Get("AppTheme", "Light"));
}
```

## 6. Reference keys with `DynamicResource` (not `StaticResource`)

```xml
<Label Text="Hello" TextColor="{DynamicResource TextPrimary}" />
<ContentPage BackgroundColor="{DynamicResource PageBackground}" />
```

**Key points:**
- `DynamicResource` is essential — it re-evaluates when the dictionary changes.
- Clearing and re-adding the merged dictionary triggers an immediate UI refresh.
- `Preferences` persists the choice across app restarts.
